.\" Manpage for bitcoin-daemon(1) — bitcoind lifecycle.
.TH BITCOIN-DAEMON 1 "2026-05-23" "bitcoin 1.22.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
bitcoin\-daemon \- enable, disable, start, stop, monitor, and inspect the local bitcoind

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bitcoin daemon
.RI [ options ]
.B enable
.RI [ --user " | " --system ]
.br
.B bitcoin daemon
.RI [ options ]
.B disable
.RI [ --user " | " --system ]
.br
.B bitcoin daemon
.RI [ options ]
.B start
.br
.B bitcoin daemon
.RI [ options ]
.B stop
.br
.B bitcoin daemon
.RI [ options ]
.B monitor
.br
.B bitcoin daemon
.RI [ options ]
.B space
.br
.B bitcoin daemon help
.RI [ command ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bitcoin daemon
provides a thin lifecycle wrapper over the Bitcoin Core
.BR bitcoind (1)
process: start it, stop it, watch its progress, and report how
much disk the chainstate is consuming. The plugin manages
.BR bitcoind
as a local long-running process and, since 1.22.0 (FEAT-034), can
install a service unit so the daemon survives reboots. It does not
run multiple instances side-by-side.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -d
Enable debug output (shell trace).
.TP
.B -q
Quiet mode (suppress info logging).

.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.BR enable " [" --user " | " --system ]
Render a service unit from the templates under
.I share/bitcoin/units/
.RB ( bitcoind.service
for systemd,
.B bitcoind.plist
for launchd), install it, and bring
.B bitcoind
up so it survives reboots.
.B --user
(default) installs a per-user service with no root
.RB ( "systemctl --user"
on Linux,
.B launchctl bootstrap gui/$UID
on macOS).
.B --system
installs a system-wide service running as a dedicated
.B bitcoin
account (created on first enable if missing) with its data dir
under
.IR /var/lib/bitcoin .
The
.BR @BITCOIND@ ", " @DATADIR@ ", and " @USER@
template markers are substituted at enable time;
.B @BITCOIND@
resolves via
.B command -v bitcoind
so a missing binary surfaces here, not later in the journal.
Idempotent. Errors with a pointer to
.B bitcoin daemon install
when no
.B bitcoind
is on PATH.
.TP
.BR disable " [" --user " | " --system ]
Tear the service down and remove its unit file. The data
directory is preserved (an explicit purge verb is left for a
future release).
.TP
.B start
Start the local
.BR bitcoind ,
respecting the user's
.I ~/.bitcoin/bitcoin.conf
configuration. Idempotent: if a daemon is already running, prints
its pid and exits 0.
.TP
.B stop
Send the configured shutdown RPC to
.BR bitcoind ;
wait for the process to exit. Idempotent.
.TP
.B monitor
Tail
.BR bitcoind 's
log and emit one progress line per new block (height, time,
sync %).
.TP
.B space
Print disk usage of the chainstate, blocks, indexes, and mempool
directories under
.IR ~/.bitcoin/ .

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B \(>=1
General error. Specific errors emit a
.B warn
or
.B error
line to stderr per CLAUDE.md §10.

.SH FILES
.TP
.I share/bitcoin/units/bitcoind.service
.TQ
.I share/bitcoin/units/bitcoind.plist
systemd and launchd unit templates rendered by
.BR enable .
.TP
.I ~/.config/systemd/user/bitcoind.service
.TQ
.I /etc/systemd/system/bitcoind.service
Installed systemd unit (\c
.B --user
and
.B --system
respectively).
.TP
.I ~/Library/LaunchAgents/org.bitcoin.bitcoind.plist
.TQ
.I /Library/LaunchDaemons/org.bitcoin.bitcoind.plist
Installed launchd unit (\c
.B --user
and
.B --system
respectively).
.TP
.I ~/.bitcoin/bitcoin.conf
Bitcoin Core configuration the daemon reads at startup.
.TP
.I ~/.bitcoin/blocks/
.TQ
.I ~/.bitcoin/chainstate/
Block and chainstate directories
.B space
reports on.
.TP
.I ~/.bitcoin/debug.log
The log
.B monitor
tails.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B SELF_DEBUG
Equivalent to
.BR -d .
.TP
.B SELF_QUIET
Equivalent to
.BR -q .
.TP
.B BITCOIN_BITCOIND
Override the
.B bitcoind
binary path used by
.BR enable ,
bypassing the
.B command -v bitcoind
PATH lookup.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bitcoin (1),
.BR bitcoin-backend (1),
.BR bitcoind (1),
.BR bitcoin-cli (1)

.SH HISTORY
Plugin introduced in bitcoin 1.0.0. Man page added in 1.23.0
(FEAT-041).
.B enable
and
.B disable
added in 1.22.0 (FEAT-034).
